The paper discusses the use of spatially coupled code ensembles, specifically convolutional LDPC ensembles, for transmission over channels with memory. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NT) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of EXIT curves, which are commonly used in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also discusses empirical evidence, which suggests that it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of low-density parity check codes, which are commonly used in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
